{"title_page": "Vadodara\u2013Kota Passenger", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox rail service\n| name = Vadodara - Kota Passenger\n| type = [[Passenger]]\n| locale = [[Gujarat]], [[Madhya Pradesh]], [[Rajasthan]]\n| first = \n| last =\n| operator = [[Western Railway Zone (India)|Western Railway]]\n| ridership =\n| start = {{rws|Vadodara Junction}} ('''BRC''')\n| stops = 61\n| end = {{rws|Kota Junction}} ('''KOTA''')\n| distance = {{convert|527|km|0|abbr=on}}\n| journeytime = 15h \n| frequency = Daily{{efn|Runs seven days in a week for every direction.}}\n| class = Unreserved \n| seating = Yes\n| sleeping = No\n| autorack =\n| catering = No\n| observation =\n| entertainment = No\n| baggage = No\n| otherfacilities=\n| stock = 2\n| gauge = {{track gauge|Indian}}\n| el =\n| train number = 59831UP/598320DN \n| speed = {{convert|35|km/h|abbr=on}} average with halts\n| map =\n| map_state =\n}}\n'''Vadodara - Kota Passenger''' is a passenger train of the Indian Railways, which runs between [[Kota Junction railway station]] in [[Rajasthan]] and [[Vadodara Junction railway station]] in [[Gujarat]]. It is currently being operated with 59831/59832 train numbers on weekly basis.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/vadodara/Repair-work-at-Vadodara-station-to-affect-rail-traffic/articleshow/47478986.cms Repair work at Vadodara station to affect rail traffic]</ref><ref>[http://www.wr.indianrailways.gov.in/view_detail.jsp?lang=0&dcd=2580&id=0,4,268 WR UNDERTAKES BLOCK FOR CC APRON REPAIR WORK AT VADODARA PF No.1 FROM 30.05.15 TO 01.06.15]</ref><ref>[http://wr.indianrailways.gov.in/view_detail.jsp?lang=0&id=0,4,268&dcd=2528&did=1431609103982E8404D74D618041E2D2ED25A57A571A8.web91 WR UNDERTAKES BLOCK FOR CC APRON REPAIR WORK AT VADODARA PF No.2 FROM 16.05.15 TO 18.05.15]</ref>\n\n== Average speed and frequency ==\n\nThe 59831/Vadodara Kota Passenger runs with an average speed of 35&nbsp;km/h and completes 527&nbsp;km in 15h. The 59832/Kota Vadodara Passenger runs with an average speed of 34&nbsp;km/h and completes 527&nbsp;km in 15h 40m. \n\n== Route & Halts ==\n\nThe important halts of the train are:\n\n* {{rws|Vadodara Junction}}\n* {{rws|Chhayapuri}}\n* {{rws|Pilol}}\n* {{rws|Samlaya Junction}}\n* {{rws|Champaner Road}}\n* {{rws|Derol}}\n* {{rws|Kharsaliya}}\n* {{rws|Godhra Junction}}\n* {{rws|Piplod}}\n* {{rws|Limkheda}}\n* {{rws|Dahod}}\n* {{rws|Bordi}}\n* {{rws|Anas}}\n* {{rws|Meghnagar}}\n* {{rws|Thandla Road}}\n* {{rws|Morwani}}\n* {{rws|Ratlam Junction}}\n* {{rws|Khachrod}}\n* {{rws|Berawanya}}\n* {{rws|Nagda Junction}}\n* {{rws|Rohal Khurd}}\n* {{rws|Mahidpur Road}}\n* {{rws|Luni Richha}}\n* {{rws|Vikramgarh Alot}}\n* {{rws|Thuria}}\n* {{rws|Bhawani Mandi}}\n* {{rws|Jhalawar Road}}\n* {{rws|Ramganj Mandi Junction}}\n* {{rws|Morak}}\n* {{rws|Kota Junction}}\n\n== Coach composite ==\n\nThe train has standard LHB rakes with max speed of 130 kmph. The train consist of 11 coaches:\n\n* 1 Chair Car\n* 7 General\n* 2 Generators cum Luggage/parcel van\n\n== Traction==\n\nBoth trains are hauls by a [[Vadodara railway station|Vadodara]] based [[WAP 4|WAP 4E]] locomotive from [[Kota, Rajasthan|Kota]] to [[Vadodara]] and vice versa.\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Kota Junction railway station]]\n* [[Vadodara Junction railway station]]\n* [[Vadodara - Dahod MEMU]]\n* [[Dahod - Ratlam MEMU]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [http://indiarailinfo.com/train/timetable/vadodara-kota-passenger-59831/3679/63/891#st 59831/Vadodara Kota Passenger]\n* [http://indiarailinfo.com/train/kota-vadodara-passenger-59832/2812/891/63 59832/Kota Vadodara Passenger]\n\n{{Railways in Western India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vadodara - Kota Passenger}}\n[[Category:Transport in Kota, Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Transport in Vadodara]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Slow and fast passenger trains in India]]\n\n\n{{India-rail-transport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox rail service\n| name = Vadodara - Kota Passenger\n| type = [[Passenger]]\n| locale = [[Gujarat]], [[Madhya Pradesh]], [[Rajasthan]]\n| first = \n| last =\n| operator = [[Western Railway Zone (India)|Western Railway]]\n| ridership =\n| start = {{rws|Vadodara Junction}} ('''BRC''')\n| stops = 61\n| end = {{rws|Kota Junction}} ('''KOTA''')\n| distance = {{convert|527|km|0|abbr=on}}\n| journeytime = 15h \n| frequency = Daily{{efn|Runs seven days in a week for every direction.}}\n| class = Unreserved \n| seating = Yes\n| sleeping = No\n| autorack =\n| catering = No\n| observation =\n| entertainment = No\n| baggage = No\n| otherfacilities=\n| stock = 2\n| gauge = {{track gauge|Indian}}\n| el =\n| train number = 59831UP/598320DN \n| speed = {{convert|35|km/h|abbr=on}} average with halts\n| map =\n| map_state =\n}}\n'''Vadodara - Kota Passenger''' is a passenger train of the Indian Railways, which runs between [[Kota Junction railway station]] in [[Rajasthan]] and [[Vadodara Junction railway station]] in [[Gujarat]]. It is currently being operated with 59831/59832 train numbers on weekly basis.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/vadodara/Repair-work-at-Vadodara-station-to-affect-rail-traffic/articleshow/47478986.cms Repair work at Vadodara station to affect rail traffic]</ref><ref>[http://www.wr.indianrailways.gov.in/view_detail.jsp?lang=0&dcd=2580&id=0,4,268 WR UNDERTAKES BLOCK FOR CC APRON REPAIR WORK AT VADODARA PF No.1 FROM 30.05.15 TO 01.06.15]</ref><ref>[http://wr.indianrailways.gov.in/view_detail.jsp?lang=0&id=0,4,268&dcd=2528&did=1431609103982E8404D74D618041E2D2ED25A57A571A8.web91 WR UNDERTAKES BLOCK FOR CC APRON REPAIR WORK AT VADODARA PF No.2 FROM 16.05.15 TO 18.05.15]</ref>\n\n== Average speed and frequency ==\n\nThe 59831/Vadodara Kota Passenger runs with an average speed of 35&nbsp;km/h and completes 527&nbsp;km in 15h. The 59832/Kota Vadodara Passenger runs with an average speed of 34&nbsp;km/h and completes 527&nbsp;km in 15h 40m. \n\n== Route & Halts ==\n\nThe important halts of the train are:\n\n* {{rws|Vadodara Junction}}\n* {{rws|Chhayapuri}}\n* {{rws|Pilol}}\n* {{rws|Samlaya Junction}}\n* {{rws|Champaner Road}}\n* {{rws|Derol}}\n* {{rws|Kharsaliya}}\n* {{rws|Godhra Junction}}\n* {{rws|Piplod}}\n* {{rws|Limkheda}}\n* {{rws|Dahod}}\n* {{rws|Bordi}}\n* {{rws|Anas}}\n* {{rws|Meghnagar}}\n* {{rws|Thandla Road}}\n* {{rws|Morwani}}\n* {{rws|Ratlam Junction}}\n* {{rws|Khachrod}}\n* {{rws|Berawanya}}\n* {{rws|Nagda Junction}}\n* {{rws|Rohal Khurd}}\n* {{rws|Mahidpur Road}}\n* {{rws|Luni Richha}}\n* {{rws|Vikramgarh Alot}}\n* {{rws|Thuria}}\n* {{rws|Bhawani Mandi}}\n* {{rws|Jhalawar Road}}\n* {{rws|Ramganj Mandi Junction}}\n* {{rws|Morak}}\n* {{rws|Kota Junction}}\n\n== Coach composite ==\n\nThe train has standard LHB rakes with max speed of 130 kmph. The train consist of 11 coaches:\n\n* 1 Chair Car\n* 7 General\n* 2 Generators cum Luggage/parcel van\n\n== Traction==\n\nBoth trains are hauls by a [[Vadodara railway station|Vadodara]] based [[WAP 4|WAP 4E]] locomotive from [[Kota]] to [[Vadodara]] and vice versa.\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Kota Junction railway station]]\n* [[Vadodara Junction railway station]]\n* [[Vadodara - Dahod MEMU]]\n* [[Dahod - Ratlam MEMU]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [http://indiarailinfo.com/train/timetable/vadodara-kota-passenger-59831/3679/63/891#st 59831/Vadodara Kota Passenger]\n* [http://indiarailinfo.com/train/kota-vadodara-passenger-59832/2812/891/63 59832/Kota Vadodara Passenger]\n\n{{Railways in Western India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vadodara - Kota Passenger}}\n[[Category:Transport in Kota, Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Transport in Vadodara]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Rajasthan]]\n[[