\n| population_density_km2          = \n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = \n| demographics1_title1            = \n| demographics1_info1             = \n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|Pincode(s)]]\n| postal_code                     = 574509.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pincode.net.in/KARNATAKA/DAKSHINA_KANNADA/P/PERMUDE|title=Postal Pincode|last=Postal|first=pincode -Permude|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n| area_code_type                  = \n| area_code                       = \n| registration_plate              = \n| blank2_name                     = \n| blank2_info                     = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n'''Permude''' is a village panchayat located in [[Mangalore taluk]] of [[Dakshina Kannada]] district in [[Karnataka]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Quarterly Journal of the All-India Institute of Local Self-Government, Bombay (Volume 66) |date=1995 |publisher=The Institute |page=201 |url=https://books.google.com/books?hl=es&id=VjC2AAAAIAAJ&dq=permude+karnataka&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Permude+Mangalore+Taluka |accessdate=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Kurukshetra, Volume 43, Issues 3-12|publisher=United Trade PressM|year=1984|isbn=|location=|pages=Page 114,115 &116}}</ref>Permude is derived from  Perda Mudde([[Tulu Language]]) as production of milk was plenty during early time.<ref>{{cite news |title=St John the Baptist Church, Permude to celebrate golden jubilee on Jan 13 |url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=375844 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=[[Daijiworld Media]] |date=10 January 2016}}</ref> [[Bangalore]] is the state capital and  It is located around 290.9 kilometer away from Permude.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Strengthening village democracy: proceedings of National Conference on Gram Sabha|first=|title=National institute of Rual Development, 2002|publisher=National Institute of Rural Development.|year=1999|isbn=|location=|pages=213,220}}</ref> The surrounding nearby villages from Permude are Bajpe, Kinnigoli.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Quarterly Journal of the Local Self-Government Institute (Bombay)|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=aJmOAAAAMAAJ&q=permude&dq=permude&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjA68GA3NXoAhV2D2MBHY-4BUM4ChDoAQhVMAU|journal=Quarterly Journal of the Local Self-Government Institute (Bombay)|volume=|pages=201|via=The Institute, 1995 - Municipal government}}</ref> According to Census 2011 information the location code or village code of Permude village is 617478.The total geographical area of village is 742.43 hectares.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Special Economic Zones in India: A Study with Special Reference to Polepally|first=|title=Special Economic Zones in India:|publisher=Daanish Books|year=2012|isbn=|location=|pages=32}}</ref>Permude also comes under [[Mangalore Special Economic Zone]] or MSEZ.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://csez.com/rti/php/sezunit_details.php?zonecode=6&pg=u|title=List of Industries and Villages under|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Daijiworld News Portal|first=|url=https://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=109246|title=Permude GP Serves Notice to MSEZ over Illegal Construction|date=|work=|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Mangalore SEZ|url=http://www.itpi.org.in/uploads/journalfiles/jan4_10.pdf|journal=Towards Greater Economic|volume=India Journal 7 - 1|pages=55|via=Institute of Town Planners, India Journal 7 - 1}}</ref>Kudubis is one of the inhabited community in Permude .Kudubis are Community that is intrinsically tribal or adivasi in nature.Customs of Kudubis are like several adivasi communities of central India.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=A REPORT OF PEOPLE\u2019S AUDIT OF SEZ KARNATAKA|first=|date=|title=A REPORT OF PEOPLE\u2019S AUDIT OF SEZ KARNATAKA|url=http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/files/KarnatakaReportfinal.pdf|journal=A REPORT OF PEOPLE\u2019S AUDIT OF SEZ KARNATAKA|volume=|pages=|via=Tata Institute of Social Sciences (TISS)}}</ref>Kudubi tribal people opposing construction of a compound wall by MSEZ.<ref>{{Cite news|last=The Hindu|first=|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Mangalore/permude-gp-stops-msez-work/article2284484.ece|title=Permude People stop construction by MSEZ|date=|work=|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pinto |first1=Stanley |title=The Mangalore Special Economic Zone (MSEZ) authorities have said the four acres of land in Kudubi Padavu... |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/The-Mangalore-Special-Economic-Zone-MSEZ-authorities-have-said-the-four-acres-of-land-in-Kudubi-Padavu-has-been-acquired-for-road-connectivity-to-Rehabilitation-and-Resettlement-RR-Colony-and-not-for-MSEZ-Industrial-purpose-A-release-from-SEZ-office-stated-that-the-land-was-notified-in-May-2007-and-acquired-in-March-2008-by-KIADB-at-the-time-of-Phase-I-land-acquisition-and-the-SEZ-was-given-the-possession-in-January-2010-/articleshow/7285409.cms |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=14 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Banks and financial institutes ==\n\n* [[Canara Bank]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bankifsccode.com/CANARA_BANK/KARNATAKA/DAKSHINA_KANNADA_/PERMUDE|title=Bank IFSC Code|last=Canara|first=Bank|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=The Bank Directory, Part 4|first=|date=|title=The Bank Directory, Part 4|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=WZUcAQAAMAAJ&q=Permude&dq=Permude&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwimuvPdoNToAhWOsRQKHdgFAvAQ6AEISTAE|journal=The Bank Directory, Part 4|volume=4|pages=2054|via=Accuity, 2007 - Bankers}}</ref>\n* [[Corporation Bank]]\n*[[Syndicate Bank]]-ATM\n\n== Schools and educational institute ==\n\n* Government Primary Urdu School\n\n== Religious institutes ==\n\n'''Temple'''\n\n* Shree Durgaparameshwari Temple Kateel\n* Ayyappa bajana mandir\n* Sri Saniseshwara Temple.\n\n'''Church'''\n\n*[[St. John the Baptist Church, Permude|St. John the Baptist Church, Permude.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=375844|title=Daijiworld- Independent News|last=Daijiworld|first=News|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dioceseofmangalore.com/parishes1/p/1193-permude|title=Discourse of Mangalore|last=Roman|first=Catholic|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n'''Mosques'''<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Muslims in Dakshina Kannada: A Historical Study Upto 1947 and Survey of Recent Developments|publisher=Green Words Publication|year=1993|isbn=|location=|pages=150}}</ref>\n\n* Jamiya Masjid\n* Minara Masjid\n*Badriya Juma Masjid.\n*Usmaniya Masjid\n\n== Transportation ==\n\n* The nearest railway station to Permude is Dokur which is located in and around 7.3 kilometer distance.\n* Mangalore railway Station is around 10.2 kilometer distance.\n* Permude's nearest airport is Mangalore International Airport situated at 5.8&nbsp;km distance.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Dakshina Kannada district]]\n\n\n{{Mangalore-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Copy edit|for=Grammar, sentence structure, readability|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Permude\n| official_name                   = Permude\n| other_name                      = \n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Gram panchayat]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   =