url=https://pincode.net.in/KARNATAKA/DAKSHINA_KANNADA/P/PERMUDE|title=Postal Pincode|last=Postal|first=pincode -Permude|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n| area_code_type                  = \n| area_code                       = \n| registration_plate              = \n| blank2_name                     = \n| blank2_info                     = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n'''Permude''' is a village panchayat located in [[Mangalore taluk]] of [[Dakshina Kannada]] district in [[Karnataka]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Quarterly Journal of the All-India Institute of Local Self-Government, Bombay (Volume 66) |date=1995 |publisher=The Institute |page=201 |url=https://books.google.com/books?hl=es&id=VjC2AAAAIAAJ&dq=permude+karnataka&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Permude+Mangalore+Taluka |accessdate=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Kurukshetra, Volume 43, Issues 3-12|publisher=United Trade PressM|year=1984|isbn=|location=|pages=Page 114,115 &116}}</ref>Permude is derived from  Perda Mudde([[Tulu Language]]) as production of milk was plenty during early time.<ref>{{cite news |title=St John the Baptist Church, Permude to celebrate golden jubilee on Jan 13 |url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=375844 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=[[Daijiworld Media]] |date=10 January 2016}}</ref> [[Bangalore]] is the state capital and  It is located around 290.9 kilometer away from Permude.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Strengthening village democracy: proceedings of National Conference on Gram Sabha|first=|title=National institute of Rual Development, 2002|publisher=National Institute of Rural Development.|year=1999|isbn=|location=|pages=213,220}}</ref> The surrounding nearby villages from Permude are Bajpe, Kinnigoli.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Quarterly Journal of the Local Self-Government Institute (Bombay)|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=aJmOAAAAMAAJ&q=permude&dq=permude&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjA68GA3NXoAhV2D2MBHY-4BUM4ChDoAQhVMAU|journal=Quarterly Journal of the Local Self-Government Institute (Bombay)|volume=|pages=201|via=The Institute, 1995 - Municipal government}}</ref> According to Census 2011 information the location code or village code of Permude village is 617478.The total geographical area of village is 742.43 hectares.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Special Economic Zones in India: A Study with Special Reference to Polepally|first=|title=Special Economic Zones in India:|publisher=Daanish Books|year=2012|isbn=|location=|pages=32}}</ref>Permude also comes under [[Mangalore Special Economic Zone]] or MSEZ.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://csez.com/rti/php/sezunit_details.php?zonecode=6&pg=u|title=List of Industries and Villages under|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Daijiworld News Portal|first=|url=https://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=109246|title=Permude GP Serves Notice to MSEZ over Illegal Construction|date=|work=|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Mangalore SEZ|url=http://www.itpi.org.in/uploads/journalfiles/jan4_10.pdf|journal=Towards Greater Economic|volume=India Journal 7 - 1|pages=55|via=Institute of Town Planners, India Journal 7 - 1}}</ref>Kudubis is one of the inhabited community in Permude .Kudubis are Community that is intrinsically tribal or adivasi in nature.Customs of Kudubis are like several adivasi communities of central India.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=A REPORT OF PEOPLE\u2019S AUDIT OF SEZ KARNATAKA|first=|date=|title=A REPORT OF PEOPLE\u2019S AUDIT OF SEZ KARNATAKA|url=http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/files/KarnatakaReportfinal.pdf|journal=A REPORT OF PEOPLE\u2019S AUDIT OF SEZ KARNATAKA|volume=|pages=|via=Tata Institute of Social Sciences (TISS)}}</ref>Kudubi tribal people opposing construction of a compound wall